from gettin' that bread!

00:10:19.411 --> 00:10:22.122 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] Who says money
can't buy motivation?

00:10:22.205 --> 00:10:24.207 position:50% align:center
Not this girl. Mm-mm!

00:10:24.290 --> 00:10:25.625 position:50% align:center
[ATTENDEES chattering, cheering]

00:10:25.709 --> 00:10:27.043 position:50% align:center
[RECEPTIONIST 1A]
From the Silverman Gym,

00:10:27.127 --> 00:10:30.672 position:50% align:center
Kibikukuri-cho branch,
Hibiki Sakura!

00:10:30.755 --> 00:10:35.385 position:50% align:center
And from the Silverman Gym,
Moscow branch, Gina Boyd!

00:10:35.468 --> 00:10:36.886 position:50% align:center
[HIBIKI]
I remember Mr. Machio saying

00:10:36.970 --> 00:10:39.431 position:50% align:center
Russia is a superpower in
the arm-wrestling world.

00:10:39.514 --> 00:10:40.724 position:50% align:center
This won't be easy.

00:10:40.807 --> 00:10:42.350 position:50% align:center
And hopefully not
too humiliating.

00:10:42.434 --> 00:10:44.310 position:50% align:center
You're not going to win.

00:10:44.394 --> 00:10:47.313 position:50% align:center
I need this money and I'm not
leaving here without it.

00:10:47.397 --> 00:10:50.275 position:50% align:center
[HIBIKI] Come on! What could
possibly be that important?

00:10:50.358 --> 00:10:52.152 position:50% align:center
Traveling here from
Russia is not cheap.

00:10:52.235 --> 00:10:54.195 position:50% align:center
I've racked up quite
the bill already.

00:10:54.279 --> 00:10:55.822 position:50% align:center
It's more expensive
here than I thought.

00:10:55.905 --> 00:10:58.408 position:50% align:center
[HIBIKI] That's it? Girl, we're
talkin' surround sound here.

00:10:58.491 --> 00:11:00.952 position:50% align:center
Are you ready?
This is the final round!

00:11:01.036 --> 00:11:04.414 position:50% align:center
Women's championship starts now!

00:11:11.421 --> 00:11:13.548 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR 6A]
Gina Boyd is 17 years old

00:11:13.631 --> 00:11:15.842 position:50% align:center
and currently
searching for love.

00:11:15.925 --> 00:11:18.470 position:50% align:center
So what's the secret behind
her winning strength?

00:11:18.553 --> 00:11:20.305 position:50% align:center
We caught up with her
at a local café

00:11:20.388 --> 00:11:22.557 position:50% align:center
and asked her this
very question.

00:11:22.640 --> 00:11:24.184 position:50% align:center
I am so glad you asked.

00:11:24.267 --> 00:11:26.978 position:50% align:center
Arm wrestling is basically
made up of two moves.

00:11:27.062 --> 00:11:28.730 position:50% align:center
The hook and the top roll.

00:11:28.813 --> 00:11:30.857 position:50% align:center
Of course, there are several
other moves you can use,

00:11:30.940 --> 00:11:32.817 position:50% align:center
but they all have elements
of these two.

00:11:32.901 --> 00:11:35.278 position:50% align:center
I guess I should explain
how each one works.

00:11:35.362 --> 00:11:36.780 position:50% align:center
Let's start with the hook.

00:11:36.863 --> 00:11:38.406 position:50% align:center
Hook your arm around
your opponent's

00:11:38.490 --> 00:11:41.326 position:50% align:center
and then lean into your
grip from above.

00:11:41.409 --> 00:11:43.453 position:50% align:center
This technique is used
by those who like to win

00:11:43.536 --> 00:11:46.581 position:50% align:center
with brute force and
minimum strategy.

00:11:46.664 --> 00:11:51.086 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Well this took a turn,
didn't it? All right.

00:11:51.169 --> 00:11:53.963 position:50% align:center
I love how beautiful
it is all year-round.

00:11:54.047 --> 00:11:55.965 position:50% align:center
Was that a trick question?

00:11:56.049 --> 00:12:00.095 position:50% align:center
Almost forgot what I was saying.
Second move is the top roll.

00:12:00.178 --> 00:12:02.138 position:50% align:center
You use your whole body
to pull, then bend

00:12:02.222 --> 00:12:05.308 position:50% align:center
their wrist down by yanking the
thumb away from their hand.

00:12:05.392 --> 00:12:07.644 position:50% align:center
Imagine their arm is
supported by a triangle.

00:12:07.727 --> 00:12:10.146 position:50% align:center
It's formed with their shoulder,
elbow, and forearm.

00:12:10.230 --> 00:12:12.482 position:50% align:center
If you break that triangle,
it throws them off balance

00:12:12.565 --> 00:12:15.485 position:50% align:center
and makes it difficult
for them to fight back.

00:12:15.568 --> 00:12:17.570 position:50% align:center
You basically force them
into a weak position

00:12:17.654 --> 00:12:20.281 position:50% align:center
so you can crush them and
you gotta be quick about it.

00:12:20.365 --> 00:12:23.201 position:50% align:center
The top roll is also
my signature move.

00:12:23.284 --> 00:12:24.994 position:50% align:center
The most common
mistake is assuming

00:12:25.078 --> 00:12:26.663 position:50% align:center
that one can win an
arm-wrestling match

00:12:26.746 --> 00:12:28.415 position:50% align:center
with arms alone.

00:12:28.498 --> 00:12:29.624 position:50% align:center
Sorry, what?

00:12:29.708 --> 00:12:31.459 position:50% align:center
You want to know my
favorite Japanese food?

00:12:31.543 --> 00:12:32.752 position:50% align:center
Uh, <i>takoyaki</i> ?

00:12:32.836 --> 00:12:35.255 position:50% align:center
Anyway, a successful
arm wrestler has more

00:12:35.338 --> 00:12:36.589 position:50% align:center
than just arm strength.

00:12:36.673 --> 00:12:38.633 position:50% align:center
They're also required to
have excellent technique!

00:12:38.717 --> 00:12:39.968 position:50% align:center
What is up with this interview?!

00:12:40.051 --> 00:12:41.386 position:50% align:center
Is she trying to put
us all to sleep?

00:12:41.469 --> 00:12:43.430 position:50% align:center
You don't have to
Russia-splain everything!

00:12:43.513 --> 00:12:46.182 position:50% align:center
[GINA] You can apply these
techniques to arm sumo as well,

00:12:46.266 --> 00:12:47.726 position:50% align:center
try them next time
you're training,

00:12:47.809 --> 00:12:50.478 position:50% align:center
but always remember to
use safety precautions.

00:12:50.562 --> 00:12:52.522 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR 6A] And so, she
continues on her journey

00:12:52.605 --> 00:12:55.775 position:50% align:center
to find a worthy opponent.
Good luck, Gina.

00:12:55.859 --> 00:12:58.361 position:50% align:center
[GINA chuckles]

00:12:58.445 --> 00:13:00.905 position:50% align:center
[GINA]
She seems to be around my age.

00:13:00.989 --> 00:13:04.034 position:50% align:center
If so, she won't be nearly
as experienced as I am.

00:13:04.117 --> 00:13:07.078 position:50% align:center
They should just hand me the
money and save some time.

00:13:07.162 --> 00:13:09.247 position:50% align:center
You look like you're
ready to begin?

00:13:09.330 --> 00:13:11.082 position:50% align:center
[GINA] Why is the
referee standing here

00:13:11.166 --> 00:13:15.462 position:50% align:center
in his under-thong?
Must be a weird Japanese thing.

00:13:15.545 --> 00:13:17.088 position:50% align:center
[MACHIO]
All right, ladies.

00:13:17.172 --> 00:13:19.341 position:50% align:center
Ready... Go!

00:13:19.424 --> 00:13:20.717 position:50% align:center
Ha!

00:13:20.800 --> 00:13:22.260 position:50% align:center
[GINA gasps]

00:13:22.344 --> 00:13:24.220 position:50% align:center
[GINA]
I can't move!

00:13:24.304 --> 00:13:25.722 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:13:25.805 --> 00:13:31.978 position:50% align:center
[GINA] I'm completely frozen!
Her strength. It's like...

00:13:32.062 --> 00:13:35.023 position:50% align:center
...the Siberian Tundra!

00:13:35.732 --> 00:13:36.483 position:50% align:center
[GINA gasps]

00:13:36.566 --> 00:13:41.154 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:13:41.237 --> 00:13:42.364 position:50% align:center
We have a winner!

00:13:42.447 --> 00:13:45.367 position:50% align:center
Congrats! Hibiki Sakura
is our champion!

00:13:45.450 --> 00:13:48.453 position:50% align:center
[HIBIKI]
Yeah! I did it!

00:13:48.536 --> 00:13:51.247 position:50% align:center
[HIBIKI laughs]

00:13:51.331 --> 00:13:52.999 position:50% align:center
[GINA]
I've been defeated.

00:13:53.083 --> 00:13:56.044 position:50% align:center
Congratulations, indeed.
Well played, Hibiki.

00:13:56.127 --> 00:13:58.129 position:50% align:center
[HIBIKI]
Hell yeah! I won!

00:13:58.213 --> 00:14:00.965 position:50% align:center
Hey Heebs, I'm gonna suggest
you buy some new clothes

00:14:01.049 --> 00:14:02.050 position:50% align:center
with that prize money first.

00:14:02.133 --> 00:14:03.259 position:50% align:center
What? Why?

00:14:03.343 --> 00:14:05.345 position:50% align:center
No! How'd my shirt get torn?!

00:14:05.428 --> 00:14:07.263 position:50% align:center
And why didn't you jerks
tell me anything sooner?

00:14:07.347 --> 00:14:08.390 position:50% align:center
[TACHIBANA]
What's going on with her?

00:14:08.473 --> 00:14:10.809 position:50% align:center
Is she part superhuman?

00:14:10.892 --> 00:14:13.269 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] Hibiki was
becoming more like Machio

00:14:13.353 --> 00:14:16.064 position:50% align:center
than she ever knew was possible.

00:14:18.191 --> 00:14:20.819 position:50% align:center
[HIBIKI groans]
I'm finally not sore!

00:14:20.902 --> 00:14:22.320 position:50% align:center
Is the world about to end?

00:14:22.404 --> 00:14:24.447 position:50% align:center
I'm still processing that
you're a wrestling champ.

00:14:24.531 --> 00:14:26.449 position:50% align:center
She frikkin
steamrolled that moose!

00:14:26.533 --> 00:14:29.828 position:50% align:center
It wasn't that easy, and I think
she may be holding a grudge.

00:14:29.911 --> 00:14:31.955 position:50% align:center
Before she left, she said...

00:14:32.038 --> 00:14:34.708 position:50% align:center
I'm sure we'll battle again
sooner than you think.

00:14:34.791 --> 00:14:37.502 position:50% align:center
[HIBIKI] Which sounds like the
bad guys in sports manga.

00:14:37.585 --> 00:14:40.088 position:50% align:center
[AYAKA] So you're like official
rivals now. Weird.

00:14:40.171 --> 00:14:42.215 position:50% align:center
[AKEMI] I really wish
I could've met her.

00:14:42.298 --> 00:14:44.300 position:50% align:center
You could always take a
trip to Russia, I guess.

00:14:44.384 --> 00:14:46.845 position:50% align:center
But I wouldn't if I were you.
They think vodka is water.

00:14:46.928 --> 00:14:48.805 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS]
Uh?

00:14:48.888 --> 00:14:51.433 position:50% align:center
Privetik! Good to see you again!

00:14:51.516 --> 00:14:53.268 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS gasping]

00:14:53.351 --> 00:14:56.813 position:50% align:center
By the way, I decided I should
study abroad at your school.

00:14:56.896 --> 00:14:58.606 position:50% align:center
I won't lose a second time.

00:14:58.690 --> 00:15:00.775 position:50% align:center
[HIBIKI] Wait, wait, wait, wait.
You moved here to get me back?

00:15:00.859 --> 00:15:02.318 position:50% align:center
Couldn't you just prank call me?

00:15:02.402 --> 00:15:04.404 position:50% align:center
It must be so fun
to have a rival!

00:15:04.487 --> 00:15:08.158 position:50% align:center
Not sure this counts as a rival.
I'm getting mad stalker vibes.

00:15:08.241 --> 00:15:09.743 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
Whether they liked it or not,

00:15:09.826 --> 00:15:13.913 position:50% align:center
Gina Boyd became the new member
of the strength-training crew.

00:15:13.997 --> 00:15:15.540 position:50% align:center
[KURE]
Good morning, everyone.

00:15:15.623 --> 00:15:16.791 position:50% align:center
May I have your attention?

00:15:16.875 --> 00:15:19.085 position:50% align:center
We have a new transfer
student in class today.

00:15:19.169 --> 00:15:22.213 position:50% align:center
Introduce yourself to your
new classmates, my dear.

00:15:22.297 --> 00:15:24.799 position:50% align:center
Hello and greetings,
Japanese student friends.

00:15:24.883 --> 00:15:26.551 position:50% align:center
I just transferred
here from Russia.

00:15:26.634 --> 00:15:28.386 position:50% align:center
My name's Gina Boyd.

00:15:28.470 --> 00:15:29.929 position:50% align:center
I'll be honest with you.

00:15:30.013 --> 00:15:31.556 position:50% align:center
I'm here for Hibiki Sakura!

00:15:31.639 --> 00:15:33.641 position:50% align:center
I challenge you, to an
arm-wrestling rematch!

00:15:33.725 --> 00:15:36.519 position:50% align:center
Right here, right now!

00:15:36.603 --> 00:15:39.814 position:50% align:center
Oh my. You're a lively one,
aren't you?

00:15:39.898 --> 00:15:42.776 position:50% align:center
Excuse me.
Hibiki's in Class B.

00:15:42.859 --> 00:15:44.778 position:50% align:center
She's actually next door.

00:15:46.446 --> 00:15:49.115 position:50% align:center
Aw, Bliat! How dare you?!

00:15:49.199 --> 00:15:51.284 position:50% align:center
What were you doing
in the other class?

00:15:51.368 --> 00:15:53.411 position:50% align:center
You're plotting against me,
aren't you, Hibiki!

00:15:53.495 --> 00:15:55.330 position:50% align:center
Look who's talking
"plotting," Russia.

00:15:55.413 --> 00:15:56.915 position:50% align:center
What the hell?

00:15:56.998 --> 00:15:59.376 position:50% align:center
It's like you flipped a switch
and became a different person!

00:15:59.459 --> 00:16:03.171 position:50% align:center
Of course I did! I can
create any persona I want!

00:16:03.254 --> 00:16:05.548 position:50% align:center
Haven't you noticed that Russian
characters in the media

00:16:05.632 --> 00:16:07.676 position:50% align:center
often fall into three
different categories?

00:16:07.759 --> 00:16:10.136 position:50% align:center
[GINA laughs]

00:16:10.220 --> 00:16:11.888 position:50% align:center
[GINA grunts]

00:16:11.971 --> 00:16:15.058 position:50% align:center
Harasho! Russia!

00:16:15.141 --> 00:16:16.601 position:50% align:center
I've been working very
hard to maintain

00:16:16.685 --> 00:16:18.645 position:50% align:center
our beloved national
stereotypes.

00:16:18.728 --> 00:16:20.230 position:50% align:center
[HIBIKI]
That girl's broken inside.

00:16:20.313 --> 00:16:21.690 position:50% align:center
[GINA] Just as the motto
of our country--

00:16:21.773 --> 00:16:23.817 position:50% align:center
coined by the great
Comrade Poutine--says,

00:16:23.900 --> 00:16:25.652 position:50% align:center
"always do your best,
no matter what."

00:16:25.735 --> 00:16:27.195 position:50% align:center
That's not an original saying!

00:16:27.278 --> 00:16:29.698 position:50% align:center
And why disrespect bears
with this screen shot?

00:16:29.781 --> 00:16:31.866 position:50% align:center
Um Gina. Did you
used to work out

00:16:31.950 --> 00:16:34.411 position:50% align:center
at the Silverman Gym in Moscow
when you lived in Russia?

00:16:34.494 --> 00:16:35.912 position:50% align:center
Da.

00:16:35.995 --> 00:16:37.580 position:50% align:center
What was your training routine
typically like out there?

00:16:37.664 --> 00:16:39.666 position:50% align:center
Are you asking about
weight training?

00:16:39.749 --> 00:16:41.418 position:50% align:center
We never did any of that stuff.

00:16:41.501 --> 00:16:42.335 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:16:42.419 --> 00:16:44.129 position:50% align:center
I promise you'll be all right.

00:16:44.212 --> 00:16:45.964 position:50% align:center
How could you? And why not?

00:16:46.047 --> 00:16:48.091 position:50% align:center
How and why would you not
do any weight training

00:16:48.174 --> 00:16:49.259 position:50% align:center
at Silverman Gym?

00:16:49.342 --> 00:16:51.428 position:50% align:center
That's a waste of a
fantastic facility!

00:16:51.511 --> 00:16:54.055 position:50% align:center
[GINA]
What is wrong with her?

00:16:54.139 --> 00:16:55.640 position:50% align:center
[GINA] I'll tell you
what I did at the gym,

00:16:55.724 --> 00:16:58.268 position:50% align:center
but you have to stop
shaking me, now!

00:16:58.351 --> 00:17:02.022 position:50% align:center
They offered a lot of classes
there, and I would take Sambo.

00:17:02.105 --> 00:17:04.983 position:50% align:center
[AYAKA] Sambo! So you're
into martial arts, too?

00:17:05.066 --> 00:17:07.152 position:50% align:center
I immediately feel
so much closer to you.

00:17:07.235 --> 00:17:08.862 position:50% align:center
Then what's with
the arm wrestling?

00:17:08.945 --> 00:17:10.321 position:50% align:center
[GINA]
Are you judging me?

00:17:10.405 --> 00:17:13.450 position:50% align:center
My Sambo buddies and I just
started doing it for fun.

00:17:13.533 --> 00:17:15.118 position:50% align:center
And until I met you,

00:17:15.201 --> 00:17:18.621 position:50% align:center
I'd never lost a battle to
anyone close to my age.

00:17:18.705 --> 00:17:20.874 position:50% align:center
So what do you think we should
do about that, Hibiki?

00:17:20.957 --> 00:17:22.917 position:50% align:center
[HIBIKI] I would say let
it go and move on?

00:17:23.001 --> 00:17:25.253 position:50% align:center
[AYAKA] She's really committing
to this whole revenge thing.

00:17:25.337 --> 00:17:26.713 position:50% align:center
[AKEMI]
I'm so confused.

00:17:26.796 --> 00:17:29.049 position:50% align:center
How can you study martial
arts but then not do any

00:17:29.132 --> 00:17:32.385 position:50% align:center
strength training?
All you do is cardio?

00:17:32.469 --> 00:17:34.429 position:50% align:center
Well no, but what the big deal?

00:17:34.512 --> 00:17:36.514 position:50% align:center
I mean. You can still
train for strength

00:17:36.598 --> 00:17:38.725 position:50% align:center
without using a
bunch of equipment.

00:17:38.808 --> 00:17:41.394 position:50% align:center
The Moscow branch didn't
have much available.

00:17:41.478 --> 00:17:43.021 position:50% align:center
We mainly did
bodyweight training

00:17:43.104 --> 00:17:45.357 position:50% align:center
with pushups, pull-ups,
squats, and deeps.

00:17:45.440 --> 00:17:46.858 position:50% align:center
Because of our
lack of equipment,

00:17:46.941 --> 00:17:48.526 position:50% align:center
we used the kipping method.

00:17:48.610 --> 00:17:50.028 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS]
What's that?

00:17:50.111 --> 00:17:52.197 position:50% align:center
It's a method that utilizes
the strength of your muscles

00:17:52.280 --> 00:17:54.282 position:50% align:center
to train them evenly.
We use momentum

00:17:54.366 --> 00:17:56.951 position:50% align:center
to increase the reps we
complete with each exercise.

00:17:57.035 --> 00:17:58.411 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:58.495 --> 00:18:00.163 position:50% align:center
That's actually a lot like
the way we train for boxing.

00:18:00.246 --> 00:18:01.790 position:50% align:center
It sounds cool,
can you teach us?

00:18:01.873 --> 00:18:04.417 position:50% align:center
Sure. I think we have enough
time before class starts.

00:18:04.501 --> 00:18:10.048 position:50% align:center
This high bar is a
perfect place for it.

00:18:10.131 --> 00:18:11.549 position:50% align:center
[GINA]
Ah!

00:18:13.176 --> 00:18:15.136 position:50% align:center
<i>Zdravstvuyte</i> ! Hello!

00:18:15.220 --> 00:18:17.472 position:50% align:center
I'm Gina Boyd, and today
I'm going to help you

00:18:17.555 --> 00:18:19.182 position:50% align:center
understand the kipping method!

00:18:19.265 --> 00:18:21.184 position:50% align:center
To my right is a chinning stand.

00:18:21.267 --> 00:18:23.186 position:50% align:center
We use it for chin-ups
and pull ups!

00:18:23.269 --> 00:18:24.646 position:50% align:center
Depending on the exercise,

00:18:24.729 --> 00:18:27.524 position:50% align:center
use either an overhand or
underhand grip on the bar.

00:18:27.607 --> 00:18:28.983 position:50% align:center
As long as you have
enough space,

00:18:29.067 --> 00:18:31.194 position:50% align:center
this is great for chin-ups
and pullups.

00:18:31.277 --> 00:18:32.862 position:50% align:center
Slowly pull your body to the top

00:18:32.946 --> 00:18:34.906 position:50% align:center
and then lower
yourself back down.

00:18:34.989 --> 00:18:37.617 position:50% align:center
Now you just did
your first chin-up.

00:18:37.701 --> 00:18:40.286 position:50% align:center
So what's the difference
between doing these exercises

00:18:40.370 --> 00:18:42.455 position:50% align:center
with and without momentum?

00:18:42.539 --> 00:18:45.125 position:50% align:center
The keyword here
is coordination!

00:18:45.208 --> 00:18:47.544 position:50% align:center
Martial artists can struggle
to build their strength

00:18:47.627 --> 00:18:50.130 position:50% align:center
with the isolated movements
of weight training.

00:18:50.213 --> 00:18:52.257 position:50% align:center
Their strength is instead
improved by practicing

00:18:52.340 --> 00:18:53.758 position:50% align:center
their techniques regularly.

00:18:53.842 --> 00:18:56.553 position:50% align:center
This also builds muscle memory
to create fluid movements.

00:18:56.636 --> 00:18:59.264 position:50% align:center
Kipping exercises are unique in
that they require momentum

00:18:59.347 --> 00:19:01.891 position:50% align:center
to work properly.
Use momentum to raise and lower

00:19:01.975 --> 00:19:04.519 position:50% align:center
your body quickly without ever
fully extending your arms.

00:19:04.602 --> 00:19:07.188 position:50% align:center
Keep the rhythm for
sets of 30 to 50.

00:19:07.272 --> 00:19:09.315 position:50% align:center
It's important to note
that this kind of training

00:19:09.399 --> 00:19:11.651 position:50% align:center
will develop your nerves
and endurance much faster

00:19:11.735 --> 00:19:12.819 position:50% align:center
than your muscle strength.

00:19:12.902 --> 00:19:14.821 position:50% align:center
But learning to coordinate
your entire body

00:19:14.904 --> 00:19:16.531 position:50% align:center
and develop controlled,
fluid movements

00:19:16.614 --> 00:19:18.908 position:50% align:center
will help you train more
efficiently overall.

00:19:18.992 --> 00:19:20.660 position:50% align:center
Traditional strength training.

00:19:20.744 --> 00:19:22.537 position:50% align:center
And exercising with momentum.

00:19:22.620 --> 00:19:24.289 position:50% align:center
They each have their benefits.

00:19:24.372 --> 00:19:26.833 position:50% align:center
Use both for maximum efficiency.

